.DT
set_response_mon_regexp
$MUDNAME$ Creator Help
set_response_mon_regexp

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
set_response_mon_regexp -  This method sets or clears the flag to use regular expressions instead of the traditional arrays of words.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void set_response_mon_regexp(int flag)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^flag%^RESET%^ - the new value of the flag: 1 says to use regular expressions,
0 to not use them

.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/living/response_mon.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method sets or clears the flag to use regular expressions instead of
the traditional arrays of words.  In addition, this flag inhibits
the usual stripping of non-alphanumerics from the input strings.
.EP

